       State Map

                   San Juan County

                                          Click a number on the map below
                                                for launch details.

                          sanjuan.gif (66551 bytes)

   Up Arrow to Map   1. Mackaye Harbor Launching Ramp

        Waterbody: Mackaye Harbor
        Site Manager: San Juan County Public Works
        Nearest City: Lopez


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Lopez Ferry S on Ferry Rd 2.1 mi; L on Center Rd, go 5.8 mi;
        continue on Mud Bay Rd, 3 mi; R on Mackaye Harbor Rd, go 1 block; R
        on unmarked Rd, ramp at end.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate to steep grade with traction hindered
        by algae growth. The concrete planks are becoming undermined by
        erosion. Steel fasteners are exposed and corroded. No designated
        disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   2. Hunter Bay Boat Ramp

        Waterbody: Hunter Bay
        Site Manager: San Juan County Public Works
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Lopez Ferry S on Ferry Rd 2.1 mi; L on Center Rd, go 5.8 mi;
        continue on Mud Bay Rd 2.2 mi; L on Island go 1.4 mi to end.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and traction is slightly hindered
        by algae growth on the concrete surface. The concrete slab has also
        developed some cracks. The right side of the ramp has an abrupt edge
        and some undermining erosion. No designated disabled parking. The
        loading float is connected to a pier. No overnight moorage at the
        loading float or the pier. Parking is limited to 72 hours.


   Up Arrow to Map   3. Island Marine Center (IMC)

        Waterbody: Fishermans Bay
        Site Manager: Ron Meng
        Nearest City: Lopez


   Site Amenities:

     Pumpout
     Water Available
     Trash Receptacles

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            2 Portable Hoist

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the Travelifts can launch/ load from mid to high tide and the
        ramp can only be used at high tide.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Lopez Ferry S on Ferry Rd (becomes Fisherman's Rd) 3 mi;
        Travelifts will be on L side of Rd.
        Site Description:

        Sand can accumulate at the ramp area. An appointment is necessary
        and a fee required for the use of the lifts. A fee is also imposed
        for the boat ramp. The Travelifts have a 15 ton capacity. No
        designated disabled parking. The marina also offers boat moorage, a
        fish cleaning station, full marine service, a lawn area, picnic
        tables, and a public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   4. Hummel Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Hummel Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Lopez Ferry S on Ferry Rd 4 mi; L "Public Fishing" sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat access has a gentle to moderate grade with a drop off at
        the shoreline. The approach to the ramp is grass. The surface
        material at the boat access point is sand. No designated disabled
        parking. There are several boats that are stored along the shore at
        the access site. A life jacket station is available for boaters to
        check out a life preserver.


   Up Arrow to Map   5. Odlin Park - Lopez Island

        Waterbody: Upright Channel
        Site Manager: San Juan County Parks Dept
        Nearest City: Lopez


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Vault
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Plank Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - low tide may restrict launching and loading on the ramp.

        Driving Directions:

        From Lopez Island Ferry Terminal, S on Ferry Rd 1.2 mi; R at Odlin
        County Park sign on Port Stanley Rd, go .1 mi to park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. Some of the concrete planks are
        broken and re-bar within the planks has become exposed. Sand and
        debris accumulates on the ramp. No designated disabled parking.
        Odlin Park also offers moorage buoys, a softball field, picnic
        tables, picnic shelter, R.V. and tent campsites, barbecue grills,
        lawn area, and public phone.


   Up Arrow to Map   6. South Beach Park (Shaw Island)

        Waterbody: Indian Cove
        Site Manager: San Juan County Parks Dept
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            5 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - cannot launch or load a trailerable boat during low tide.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Shaw Ferry, go 1.2 mi on Blind Bay Rd; L on Squaw Bay Rd, go
        .75 mi; L at Public Camping sign.
        Site Description:

        The sand beach launch has a gentle grade. The boat access has a wood
        plank and concrete approach down to the beach. A wood plank is
        broken and concrete is breaking apart on the approach. No designated
        disabled parking. South Beach Park also offers campsites, lawn area,
        picnic shelter, and play equipment. No fee to use the boat ramp, but
        an overnight parking fee is charged to boats that are out for more
        than a day ($4.00/ day).


   Up Arrow to Map   7. Obstruction Pass Launching Ramp

        Waterbody: Obstruction Pass
        Site Manager: San Juan County Parks Dept
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Concrete Ramp
                                   1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     15 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   6 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Orcas Ferry, follow Horseshoe Highway 16 mi to Olga; L on
        Point Lawrence Rd, go .75 mi; R on Obstruction Pass Rd, go 1.5 mi;
        ramp on L.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. Sand and gravel
        accumulate on the boat ramp. As a result, traction is hindered by
        the loose sand and gravel. No designated disabled parking. Boat
        trailer parking is for day-use only. Other parking is limited to 72
        hours. This site is next to Lieber Haven Resort which offers a store
        and boat moorage. No overnight moorage on the county owned loading
        float.


   Up Arrow to Map   8. Rosario Resort

        Waterbody: Cascade Bay
        Site Manager: Natural Resources Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - low tide at or below 0 feet could restrict access to the rest
        of the marina and out to the sound.

        Driving Directions:

        On Horseshoe Highway 13.3 mi from ferry, R on Rosario Rd to resort.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a steep grade. Traction is hindered on the lower
        end of the ramp by algae growing on the ramp surface. The ramp is
        located in protected waters at the end of the cove. Parking around
        the ramp is only available to registered guests of the resort.
        Rosario Resort also offers boat moorage, store, cafe, hotel, play
        equipment, lawn area, public phone, and flush restrooms.


   Up Arrow to Map   9. Bartwood Lodge

        Waterbody: President Channel
        Site Manager: Bartwood Lodge
        Nearest City: Eastsound


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  1 Concrete Ramp
                                  1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     38 Paved and Striped Spaces

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  None

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        On Horseshoe Highway, pass Eastsound; R on Mt. Baker Rd, go .25 mi;
        L on N Beach Rd, go .5 mi; R on Anderson Rd, go .75 mi to resort
        sign.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. The
        concrete slab is broken and cracked at mid-ramp. Undermining erosion
        is occurring at the upper section of the ramp. The location of the
        ramp does not offer much protection from inclimate weather
        influences. Bartwood Lodge also offers 16 motel resort rooms, a
        restaurant, bar, fishing tours, wildlife excursions, shuttles to
        Sucia and Matia islands, public phone, a lawn area, and tennis
        courts. The center isle in the parking lot could accommodate eight
        vehicles with trailers. A fee is charged to launch ($10.00 - round
        trip).


   Up Arrow to Map   10. West Beach Resort

        Waterbody: President Channel
        Site Manager: West Beach Resort
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - Luanch and loading may be difficult at or below a 0 ft. tide.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Orcas Ferry, N on Horseshoe Highway .75 mi past Eastsound; L
        on Enchanted Forest, go 2.5 mi to intersection; go straight,then R
        to resort.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp is available to the registered guests and by an
        appointment. West Beach Resort also offers moorage, boat rentals, a
        fish cleaning station, SCUBA air refills, R.V. campsites with
        electrical and water hook-ups, tent campsites, store, bait and
        tackle, rental cabins, restrooms, showers, and sea kayak tours. A
        fee is charged for the use of the boat ramp and trailer parking
        ($10.00 day). No designated disabled parking.


   Up Arrow to Map   11. West Sound Marina

        Waterbody: White Beach Bay
        Site Manager: West Sound Marina
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Portable Hoist
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            20 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Orcas Ferry N on Horseshoe Highway 2.3 mi; L on Deer Harbor
        Rd, go .5 mi; L at W Sound Marina to Travelift.
        Site Description:

        A fee is charged for the use of the Travelift (cost depends on the
        size of the vessel). No designated disabled parking. West Sound
        Marina also offers moorage and marine supplies and services. The
        Travelift capacity is 30 tons or 65 feet.


   Up Arrow to Map   12. Jackson Beach Park (Friday Harbor)

        Waterbody: North Bay (San Juan Island)
        Site Manager: Friday Harbor Port of
        Nearest City: Friday Harbor


   Site Amenities:

     None

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     5 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            12 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - low tides may restrict the use of the ramp for some boats.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave ferry in Friday Harbor on Spring St .1 mi, L on Argyle Ave, go
        .75 mi; L on Pear Point Rd, go .5 mi; R on Jackson Beach Rd, go .25
        mi to access area.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. The
        concrete slab is broken at the top of the ramp and at mid-ramp.
        There are abrupt edges on the right side of the ramp and at the end
        of the ramp. No designated disabled parking. Vehicles and trailers
        left in the parking area over 72 hours are subject to impoundment.
        The loading float is beginning to deteriorate (holes in the
        decking). Jackson Beach Park also has beach access, day-use parking,
        a few picnic tables, and a sani-can. A marine preserve is located
        north of the boat ramp. Car parking can be found in the day-use
        beach area.


   Up Arrow to Map   13. Sportsman Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Sportsman Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Natural Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   3 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Friday Harbor high school, N on Tucker Ave. (becomes Roche
        Harbor Rd), 3.5 mi; L on unmarked gravel drive, go 150 ft. to ramp
        at end.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle grade. The ramp surface is sand and
        gravel. The drive and the ramp are uneven due to vehicle use. No
        designated disabled parking. Parking is primarily along the Roche
        Harbor Road.


   Up Arrow to Map   14. Roche Harbor Resort

        Waterbody: Roche Harbor
        Site Manager: Roche Harbor Marina
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            50 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - low tides may restrict launching and loading of some boats.

        Driving Directions:

        In Friday Harbor at high school, N on Tucker Ave.; veer L at 'Y' on
        Roche Harbor Rd, go 10 mi; at end of county Rd, turn L; follow Rd to
        end.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade with adequate traction.
        An abrupt edge exists on the left side. The concrete slab also has
        cracks. A gate at the ramp requires users to pay before using. A fee
        is required to use the boat ramp ($14.00 trailerable boat, round
        trip/ $8.00 trailerable boat, one way,/ $7.00 smaller craft). Roche
        Harbor Marina also offers moorage, a grocery store, public
        restrooms, picnic area, hotel, cabins, gift shops, a public phone,
        transient moorage, showers and laundry facility. Parking for
        vehicles with trailers is located above the resort/ marina complex.


   Up Arrow to Map   15. Snug Harbor Resort and Marina

        Waterbody: Mitchell Bay
        Site Manager: Snug Harbor Resort and Marina
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Fuel Available
     Water Available

                          Boat Launch Type:

                            1 Concrete Ramp
                            1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     10 Gravel Spaces

                          Trailer Parking Facilities:

                            15 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - the ramp may become difficult at minus tides depending on the
        boat.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Friday Harbor ferry terminal on Spring St, go 2 blocks; R on
        2nd St.; go straight for 7 mi; L on Mitchell Bay Rd, go 2.5 mi.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and adequate traction. The
        concrete slab is cracked and breaking apart at the end. Snug Harbor
        Resort and Marina also offers boat moorage, boat rentals, fishing
        charters, whale watching tours, kayak rentals, SCUBA air refills, a
        convenience store, tent and RV campsites, motel rooms, a public
        phone, limited shower access, propane, picnic area, and restroom
        facility. No designated disabled parking. Additional parking can be
        found along Mitchell Bay Road.


   Up Arrow to Map   16. San Juan County Park

        Waterbody: Small Pox Bay
        Site Manager: San Juan County Parks Dept
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     Restroom - Portable Sani Can

                                 Boat Launch Type:

                                   1 Concrete Ramp

   Car Parking Facilities:

     None

                                 Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                   10 Gravel Spaces

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        yes - low tide may restrict the use of the ramp for launching and
        loading.

        Driving Directions:

        Leave Friday Harbor ferry on Spring St 2 blocks; R on 2nd St, go
        straight 7 mi; L on Mitchell Bay Rd, go 1.5 mi, becomes Westside Rd,
        follow 2 miles to Park.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a gentle to moderate grade. The ramp is located in
        a cove that provides some protection. The concrete slab was poured
        in the summer of 1997. No designated disabled parking. Small Pox Bay
        Park also offers R.V., tent, and group campsites, along with a
        bicycle, kayak, and hiker camp area. A day-use facility provides
        lawn areas, picnic tables, picnic shelter, public restrooms, and
        barbecue grills. Car parking is located above the ramp area near the
        campground.


   Up Arrow to Map   17. Egg Lake (WDFW)

        Waterbody: Egg Lake
        Site Manager: Fish & Wildlife Dept of
        Nearest City:


   Site Amenities:

     None

                                Boat Launch Type:

                                  1 Gravel Ramp
                                  1 Loading Float

   Car Parking Facilities:

     2 Paved Spaces, No Striping

                                Trailer Parking Facilities:

                                  1 Paved Spaces, No Striping

        Seasonal Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Tidal or Water Limitations:

        No known limitations

        Driving Directions:

        From Friday Harbor high school, N on Tucker Ave (becomes Roche
        Harbor Rd), 4 mi; L on Egg Lake Rd, go 1 mi; ramp area on L.
        Site Description:

        The boat ramp has a moderate grade and an even surface. The ramp is
        only suitable for smaller watercraft. No designated disabled
        parking. This site is provided courtesy of WDFW, San Juan Island
        Parks and Recreation District, and the San Juan Lions Club.



